This memorandum is a delegation of authority from President Joseph R. Biden Jr. to the Secretary of State under section 506(a)(1) of the Foreign Assistance Act of 1961. The Secretary of State is granted the authority to direct the drawdown of up to $2.5 billion in defense articles and services, as well as military education and training, to provide assistance to Ukraine. The Secretary of State is also responsible for making the necessary determinations required under section 506(a)(1) to carry out this drawdown. The memorandum directs the publication of this delegation of authority in the Federal Register.